benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Remove tags from account

covered: Valid deletion scenarios are covered: TC01 (single tag), TC02 (multiple tags), TC03 (all tags) and TC04 (with extra headers) demonstrate 204 responses and tag removal; TC05 confirms behavior when account has no tags.
Header/auth boundary covered: tests require X-Killbill-CreatedBy in allowed requests and include a missing-header case (TC09) and unauthorized case (TC15).
Input validation and error handling: TC06 (non-existent account), TC07 (invalid accountId format), TC08 (invalid tagDef), TC14 (malformed tagDef) and TC09 (missing header).
Edge cases and parameter handling: TC11 (unexpected query params), TC13 (large number of tagDefs), TC20 (empty tagDef array), TC03 (no tagDef) as removing all tags.
Resilience and service availability: TC12 (service down) and TC16 (network interruption) test 5xx errors and recovery; TC17 tests concurrency and performance.
Regression and compatibility: TC18 (mixed valid/invalid tagDefs) and TC19 (omitting optional headers) test regression and backward compatibility.
gaps: Soft delete semantics (whether deletion is soft or hard) is not tested.
Rate limiting/throttling scenarios are not tested.
Pagination is not applicable to deletion but not tested for related endpoints; consider adding tests for listing endpoints.
Explicit 404 Not Found case for non-existent account is not covered (tests use 400 for non-existent).
Duplicate tagDef parameters or complex parameter ordering beyond tested scenarios are not covered.
recommendations: Add tests verifying caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on DELETE responses.
Introduce rate-limiting tests to ensure resilience under burst traffic.
Add tests to validate soft-delete semantics or confirm hard deletion semantics as intended.
Add a 404-specific test for deleting tags from a non-existent account to align REST conventions and clarify error semantics.
Add tests for duplicate tagDef query parameters to ensure idempotent behavior and proper handling of duplicates.
Expand authorization testing to include expired tokens or insufficient privileges with explicit 401/403 responses.
